Global setup:
 Download and install Git
  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
  git config --global user.email michaelthecsguy@gmail.com
        
Next steps:
  mkdir dotVimVundle
  cd dotVimVundle
  git init
  touch README
  git add README
  git commit -m 'first commit'
  git remote add origin git@github.com:michaelthecsguy/dotVimVundle.git
  git push -u origin master
      
Existing Git Repo?
  cd existing_git_repo
  git remote add origin git@github.com:michaelthecsguy/dotVimVundle.git
  git push -u origin master

Installation for NEW Environment:

  git clone git://github.com/michaelthecsguy/dotVimVundle.git ~/.vim

Create Symlinks:

  ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
  ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
